Description: Lower half of pink sandstone shabti of Setau, Viceroy of Nubia represented wearing triangular apron; Hieroglyphic text includes sehedj-formula on front, and Khaemwaset formula on sides and originally on back.
Curator's comments: Published Kitchen, Ram. Insc. Vol 3 p111. Cf. examples of Khaemwaest: Prisse d'Avennes, Mon. Eg. (Paris 1847), pl. XX.
Acquisition name: Purchased from: George Annesley, 2nd Earl of Mountnorris
